What you need to know:  Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP) Noordin Haji has refuted claims that his office only considered ethnic and religious backgrounds for 28 positions to be filled later this month.The DPP’s office advertised the positions including assistant directors of supplies, administration and human resource management, and finance officers in June last year.A total of 2,031 people applied at the close of the exercise on June 17, 2021. The DPP’s office later shortlisted 148 persons, for interviews set to begin on April 25.